From: DevBox UML arm64 Port
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] arm64/um: add Makefile.um for UML build system entry point

arch/um/Makefile includes arch/$(SUBARCH)/Makefile.um at build time.
Without this file, ARCH=um builds fail immediately on aarch64 with
"No such file or directory" before any compilation begins.

This adds the minimal Makefile.um for arm64, defining:
- SUBARCH flags for the UML host userspace layer
- ELF format for the generated kernel binary
- Stub symbol names used by the fault injection mechanism

diff --git a/arch/arm64/Makefile.um b/arch/arm64/Makefile.um
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/arch/arm64/Makefile.um
@@ -0,0 +1,20 @@
+# SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0
+# arch/arm64/Makefile.um — UML (User Mode Linux) build glue for arm64 hosts.
+# Included by arch/um/Makefile when SUBARCH=aarch64/arm64.
+
+START_ADDR ?= 0x400000
+
+# Flags for the UML host-side userspace objects (not the guest kernel)
+SUBARCH_CFLAGS  := -D__arch_um__ -DSUBARCH=\"arm64\" \
+                   -fno-builtin
+SUBARCH_AFLAGS  :=
+SUBARCH_LDFLAGS :=
+
+# Output binary format
+ELF_ARCH   := aarch64
+ELF_FORMAT := elf64-littleaarch64
+
+# Stub symbols — used by arch/um/kernel/skas/uaccess.c
+# stub_segv is a small trampoline mapped into each UML process for
+# delivering faults back to the kernel thread.
+STUB_START = stub_segv
+STUB_END   = stub_end
